Day-9 Topics
1️⃣ What is Concurrency Problem?

When multiple requests update same account at same time.

Example:

Balance = 1000

Thread-1 withdraw 800
Thread-2 withdraw 500 (same time)

Both read balance = 1000 ❌
Final balance = -300 💥


This is called Race Condition.

2️⃣ Real Banking Problems

Without locking:

❌ Double withdrawal

❌ Negative balance

❌ Lost update

❌ Inconsistent balance

Banks MUST prevent this.

3️⃣ Locking Types (Very Important)
A. Optimistic Locking (High performance)

Assumes conflict is rare.

Uses @Version column.

If two updates happen → one fails → retry.

Used in:

Wallet

Payments

High-scale banking

B. Pessimistic Locking (Bank-grade safety)

Locks row in DB (SELECT ... FOR UPDATE)

Other transactions must WAIT.

Used in:

Core banking

Money transfer

Ledger updates

