🔒 Pessimistic Locking (FOR UPDATE)

Goal: Prevent other transactions from reading/modifying the same row until your transaction finishes.
Used when conflicts are likely and you must guarantee no concurrent modification.

🧠 How it works

When you fetch a row using SELECT ... FOR UPDATE:

DB locks that row immediately

Other transactions trying to:

UPDATE → will wait

SELECT ... FOR UPDATE → will wait

Normal SELECT → depends on isolation level (usually allowed, but no write)

Lock released only after COMMIT / ROLLBACK

📌 SQL Example
START TRANSACTION;

SELECT * FROM account WHERE id = 1 FOR UPDATE;

-- Now row is locked
UPDATE account SET balance = balance - 500 WHERE id = 1;

COMMIT;

