Here is the Isolation Level Demo (Spring Boot + MySQL) — very important for banking / microservices interviews.

🧠 Isolation Level Demo

Isolation level controls how transactions see each other’s data.

Types (Interview must-know)

READ_UNCOMMITTED → Dirty reads possible

READ_COMMITTED → No dirty read (Default in most DBs)

REPEATABLE_READ → Same row value in same transaction (MySQL default)

SERIALIZABLE → Fully locked, safest, slowest

🧪 Problem to Demonstrate

We simulate Non-Repeatable Read

Tx-1 reads balance = 1000

Tx-2 updates balance = 500 and commits

Tx-1 reads again → sees different value (problem)

🏗 Entity
@Entity
@Data
public class Account {

    @Id
    private Long id;

    private double balance;
}

🧾 Repository
